New Delhi : The CVC has received fresh complaints related to 2G scam in which new names of bureaucrats , both serving and retired , have cropped up and the anti - corruption watchdog has forwarded them to the CBI for further investigation . Highly placed sources said the Central Vigilance Commission has received complaints recently against former Telecom Minister A Raja and certain serving and retired Telecom Ministry officials for alleged violation of Government norms in spectrum allocation during their tenure . They said the complaints were forwarded to the CBI to cross check their authenticity and take necessary action .